# Windows shells REQUIRE CRLF in batch files. rag.bat sat in the tree with
# LF-only endings and cmd.exe mis-parsed it into garbage tokens
# ("'M' is not recognized as an internal or external command"), which reads as
# a broken install rather than a line-ending problem. Pin it so a checkout on
# any machine, and any tool that rewrites these files, produces CRLF.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
